com.basho.riak.client.jiak
Class JiakObject

java.lang.Object
  com.basho.riak.client.jiak.JiakObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
RiakObject
public class JiakObject
extends java.lang.Object
implements RiakObject

Implementation of RiakObject which interprets objects retrieved from Riak's Jiak interface. Internally, the value, links, and user-defined metadata are all stored as JSON objects and converted to their Java object equivalents on request.

getLinksAsJSON

public org.json.JSONArray getLinksAsJSON()
Returns the object's links serialized as JSON. A link in Jiak consists of an array with three elements: the target bucket, target key, and link tag. Links added to this array will not be included in the Jiak object.

Specified by:
getUsermeta in interface RiakObject

getUsermetaAsJSON

public org.json.JSONObject getUsermetaAsJSON()
Returns the usermeta map serialized to a JSONObject. Data added to this object will not be included in the Jiak object.

setUsermeta

public void setUsermeta(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> usermeta)
Anything set here will be added to the "usermeta" field of the value since Jiak does not currently support storing user-defined metadata in a separate field. It only stores links and the object value.
